description:
This well presented 2 storey, 2 bedroom unit is in a great location that is situated walking distance to several restaurants, Cafes, Schools and many other business to simplify your lifestyle.

The downstairs open plan living area is fully tiled and includes a spacious lounge, dining and kitchen with air conditioning. The modern kitchen features quality appliances and a dishwasher. Underneath the steps is an extra storage cabinet. The laundry is large enough to house a linen cabinet and leads directly out to the backyard.

Upstairs features beautiful timber hardwood floors throughout. The master bedroom featuring a walk-in wardrobe and split system air-conditioning and a private balcony. The other bedroom has a built-in wardrobe and fan. The generous sized bathroom has a large shower and vanity.

Property Summary:
- 2 good sized bedrooms all with wardrobes, ceiling fans, and one with split system air-conditioning
- Kitchen with ample of storage space, dishwasher and electric stove/cooktop
- Tiled airconditioned open plan living and dining
- Security screens on all external accessible doors and windows
- Recently painted inside
- Single carport with council approval
- Separate laundry and access to the backyard
- 107sqm allotment with only one conjoining wall, fully fenced and side access

Rental appraisal $350 - $370 per week.

Conveniently located, you can walk to the beach, Evans Street Shops, schools (both public & private), a short drive into the CBD and airport, all the conveniences at your fingertips, but quietly located away from the hustle and bustle.

Give Sales Agent Kelsey Webb a call today on 0407 997 021 for more information.
